<item>
            <title>[SPARK-20997] spark-submit&apos;s --driver-cores marked as &quot;YARN-only&quot; but listed under &quot;Spark standalone with cluster deploy mode only&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-20997</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Just noticed that &lt;tt&gt;spark-submit&lt;/tt&gt; describes &lt;tt&gt;--driver-cores&lt;/tt&gt; under:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Spark standalone with cluster deploy mode only&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;YARN-only&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;While I can understand &quot;only&quot; in &quot;Spark standalone with cluster deploy mode only&quot; to refer to cluster deploy mode (not the default client mode), but YARN-only baffles me which I think deserves a fix.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
